The paper proposes a learning-based framework for video compression, which involves modeling spatiotemporal coherence and performing predictive coding inside the learning network. This suggests that the paper could belong to the Multimedia (cs.MM), Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition (cs.CV), Information Theory (cs.IT), Machine Learning (cs.LG), or Artificial Intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Among these, cs.MM and cs.CV are the most likely sub-categories, as they are directly related to video processing and analysis. cs.IT is also likely, as it deals with data compression and transmission. cs.LG and cs.AI are less likely, but still possible, as they involve machine learning techniques used in the proposed framework.
